This article is a statement made by the President of the United States on Armenian Remembrance Day. The President solemnly remembers the events that occurred 96 years ago, resulting in the mass killing and deportation of 1.5 million Armenians during the final days of the Ottoman Empire. The President emphasizes the importance of acknowledging the historical facts and the need for a full and just acknowledgement of the atrocities. He states that contested history destabilizes the present and dishonors the memory of those who lost their lives. The President supports the efforts of individuals in Armenia and Turkey to foster a dialogue that acknowledges their common history. He also pays tribute to the Armenian-American community and recognizes their contributions to the United States. The President reiterates the commitment to ensuring that such devastating events are never repeated and expresses solidarity with Armenians worldwide.